page.title: 08FISH
page.content: The fish in are area are mostly small such as the minnow which is normanlly found in lakes and meanders where the water force is not too great.Sticklebacks and bullheads prefer rivers and streams where the current is quite fast.The stone boach hurks in shadows under banks that over hang the river on skulk in the weeds on the river or streams bed.All these small fish that inhabit the areas rivers rely on the river for good. Big fish such as the trout livein lakes and farely deep rivers and streams.There are two kinds of trout in the area they are brown trout and rainbow trout.These are sometimes stocked in trout pools.There are three trout pools in the area but they are private.
